Starting with OpenCTI 6.0, a Max Confidence Level will be added to groups and users. It will provide platform administrators with more control on the impact of imported data and prevent any unwanted update on data. Please read {link_blogpost} for more information.
 
On this platform, "Max Confidence Level" of some groups are currently undefined. Their members will not be able to create any data in version 6.X of the platform. In order to prevent that, make sure that all groups have a Max Confidence Level set. More info in {link_blogpost}. Be particularly mindful of users associated to Connectors, Feeds and Streams; you can set individual confidence level to override group confidence level if needed. Join {link_slack} if you need advices.
